:ThisPaper :proposes :GroundingDINO ;
    :contextText "we develop an open-set object detector, called Grounding DINO" .

:ThisPaper :addresses :OpenSetObjectDetection ;
    :contextText "detect arbitrary objects specified by human language inputs, a task commonly referred to as open-set object detection" .

:GroundingDINO :basedOn :DINO ;
    :contextText "marrying Transformer-based detector DINO with grounded pre-training" .

:GroundingDINO :uses :TightModalityFusion ;
    :contextText "we design the strong open-set object detector Grounding DINO by following the two principles: tight modality fusion based on DINO" .

:GroundingDINO :partOf :FeatureEnhancer ;
    :contextText "which includes a feature enhancer, a language-guided query selection, and a cross-modality decoder" .

:GroundingDINO :partOf :LanguageGuidedQuerySelection ;
    :contextText "which includes a feature enhancer, a language-guided query selection, and a cross-modality decoder" .

:GroundingDINO :partOf :CrossModalityDecoder ;
    :contextText "which includes a feature enhancer, a language-guided query selection, and a cross-modality decoder" .

:GroundingDINO :uses :SubSentenceTextRepresentation ;
    :contextText "we introduce attention masks to block attentions among unrelated category names, named “sub-sentence” level representation" .

:GroundingDINO :uses :SwinT ;
    :contextText "Grounding DINO T with Swin-T ... as an image backbone" .

:GroundingDINO :uses :SwinL ;
    :contextText "Grounding DINO L with Swin-L ... as an image backbone" .

:GroundingDINO :uses :BERTBase ;
    :contextText "We leveraged BERT-base ... as text backbones." .

:FeatureEnhancer :uses :TextToImageCrossAttention ;
    :contextText "we add an image-to-text and a text-to-image cross-attention modules for feature fusion" .

:FeatureEnhancer :uses :ImageToTextCrossAttention ;
    :contextText "we add an image-to-text and a text-to-image cross-attention modules for feature fusion" .

:CrossModalityDecoder :uses :DeformableAttention ;
    :contextText "We leverage deformable attention [ 62] in image cross-attention layers." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "900 queries" ;
    :contextText "In alignment with the DINO method, we set Nq to be 900." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "max 256 text tokens" ;
    :contextText "We set the maximum text token number as 256." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "feature dimension d=256" ;
    :contextText "we speciﬁcally utilize a feature dimension of d= 256." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "6 feature enhancer layers" ;
    :contextText "We use six feature enhancer layers in the feature enhancer module." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "6 decoder layers" ;
    :contextText "The cross-modality decoder is composed of six decoder layers as well." .

:GroundingDINO :uses :L1Loss ;
    :contextText "we use the L1 loss ... for bounding box regressions." .

:GroundingDINO :uses :GIoULoss ;
    :contextText "we use the L1 loss and the GIOU [ 39] loss for bounding box regressions." .

:GroundingDINO :uses :FocalLoss ;
    :contextText "then compute focal loss [ 27] for each logit." .

:GroundingDINO :uses :ContrastiveLoss ;
    :contextText "we follow GLIP [ 24] and use contrastive loss between predicted objects and language tokens for classiﬁcation." .

:GroundingDINO :uses :HungarianMatching ;
    :contextText "Following DINO, we set the weight of classiﬁcation costs, box L1 costs, and GIOU costs as 2.0, 5.0, and 2.0, respectively, during Hungarian matching." .

:HungarianMatching :relatedTo "classification cost weight 2.0" ;
    :contextText "we set the weight of classiﬁcation costs, box L1 costs, and GIOU costs as 2.0, 5.0, and 2.0, respectively, during Hungarian matching." .

:HungarianMatching :relatedTo "box L1 cost weight 5.0" ;
    :contextText "we set the weight of classiﬁcation costs, box L1 costs, and GIOU costs as 2.0, 5.0, and 2.0, respectively, during Hungarian matching." .

:HungarianMatching :relatedTo "GIoU cost weight 2.0" ;
    :contextText "we set the weight of classiﬁcation costs, box L1 costs, and GIOU costs as 2.0, 5.0, and 2.0, respectively, during Hungarian matching." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "classification loss weight 1.0" ;
    :contextText "The corresponding loss weights are 1.0, 5.0, and 2.0 in the ﬁnal loss calculation." .

:GroundingDINO :uses "box L1 loss weight 5.0" ;
